I've created a comprehensive testing and quality assurance setup for the Solana KYC Compliance SDK:

✅ Complete Testing Suite:

1. Rust Program Tests:
   · Unit Tests: Instruction packing/unpacking, state serialization, error mapping
   · Integration Tests: Local validator flow, program interaction
   · Token Extensions Tests: Integration with SPL Token 2022
2. TypeScript SDK Tests:
   · Unit Tests: Client methods, instruction builders, utilities, error handling
   · Integration Tests: End-to-end compliance flow with local validator
   · Mock Data: Comprehensive test fixtures and scenarios
3. CI/CD Setup:
   · GitHub Actions: Full CI pipeline with linting, building, testing
   · Multi-job workflows: Separate Rust and TypeScript test runs
   · Coverage reporting: Codecov integration with badges
   · Security scanning: npm audit, cargo audit, Snyk integration
   · Performance benchmarking: Automated performance tests
4. Quality Assurance Tools:
   · ESLint: TypeScript linting with strict rules
   · Prettier: Code formatting
   · Mocha/Chai: Test framework with good reporting
   · NYC: Code coverage for TypeScript
   · Cargo Tarpaulin: Rust code coverage

Key Testing Features:

1. Comprehensive Coverage:
   · Instruction validation and error cases
   · State serialization/deserialization
   · PDA generation correctness
   · Transfer validation scenarios
   · Policy enforcement logic
2. Realistic Scenarios:
   · Compliant and non-compliant transfers
   · Country restrictions and KYC levels
   · Freeze/unfreeze operations
   · Policy updates and admin functions
   · Batch operations performance
3. Developer Experience:
   · Easy local testing with scripts/test-local.sh
   · Coverage reporting with scripts/coverage.sh
   · Performance benchmarking with scripts/benchmark.sh
   · Clear test organization and fixtures
4. Production Readiness:
   · Automated security scanning
   · Weekly scheduled test runs
   · PR validation with multiple test types
   · Coverage requirements enforcement
   · Performance regression detection

Test Commands:

```bash
# Run all tests
npm run test:all

# Run TypeScript unit tests
npm test

# Run integration tests
npm run test:integration

# Run Rust tests
npm run test:rust

# Local testing with validator
./scripts/test-local.sh

# Generate coverage report
./scripts/coverage.sh

# Run benchmarks
./scripts/benchmark.sh
```

CI/CD Pipeline Features:

1. Automated Quality Gates:
   · Code linting and formatting
   · Type checking and compilation
   · Unit and integration tests
   · Security vulnerability scanning
   · Code coverage requirements
2. Multi-Platform Testing:
   · Rust program on Solana BPF
   · TypeScript SDK in Node.js
   · Integration with local validator
   · Token extensions compatibility
3. Reporting and Metrics:
   · Test results in JUnit format
   · Code coverage reports to Codecov
   · Performance benchmarks
   · Security scan results
4. Release Readiness:
   · Automated version checking
   · Release tag creation
   · Artifact generation
   · Documentation updates

This testing setup ensures the SDK is:

· Reliable: Comprehensive test coverage
· Secure: Regular security scanning
· Performant: Performance benchmarking
· Maintainable: Code quality enforcement
· Production-ready: CI/CD with quality gates

The system is ready for enterprise adoption with professional-grade testing and quality assurance practices.